[[htmlelements">
== HTML Standard Elements
	
		The following defines standard HTML elements. If you want to try out
		these
		elements, take the example of your first webpage and place the
		new
		tags between the <![CDATA[ <body> </body> ]]>
		tag. Save your file and re-load your browser to see the result.
	
[[htmlelements_blocks">
=== Blocks and structural elements
		<![CDATA[ <p> </p> ]]>
			describes a paragraph and <![CDATA[ <h1> </h1> ]]>
			a headline. You have six headlines available from  <![CDATA[ <h1> </h1> ]]>
			to <![CDATA[ <h6> </h6> ]]>.
		
		 <![CDATA[ <br/> ]]>
			describes a line break. Please note that this tag is directly closed
			via the slash at the end. <![CDATA[ <br> </br> ]]>
			is incorrect. <![CDATA[ <hr/> ]]>
			inserts a line into the text.
		

[[htmlelements_tags">
=== HTML Links
		 The following describes a link in HTML. The attribute "href"
			defines the target
			of the link. A link can be absolute or relativ to
			the existing
			webpage.
		

		
			<programlisting>
				<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
					parse="text" href="./examples/html/anchor.txt[]
----
		

		 The following listing contains a link which displays a image.
		
		
			<programlisting>
				<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
					parse="text" href="./examples/html/imagelink.txt[]
----
		
		 The following example shows how to create a link for an email.
		
		
			<programlisting>
				<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
					parse="text" href="./examples/html/emaillink.txt[]
----
		
		

